channel.title: ASF JIRA
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HBASE-22893] Change the comment in HBaseClassTestRule to reflect change in default test timeouts
item.description:
The default timeout is 13 minutes. Change the comment accordingly.

        // All tests have a 10minute timeout.
item.summary: Change the comment in HBaseClassTestRule to reflect change in default test timeouts

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Hi jatsakthi I changed the comment present in HBaseClassTestRule from "All tests have a 10minute timeout" to "All tests have 13 minutes timeout". Is it necessary to search for the similar kind of comments in other files as well??
I don't think there are any other occurrences of such comments. Please double check. If you feel comfortable, please put up a patch for the same (or a git PR if you would like so).
Thank you for the response. I did check in the whole project but didn't find any. I have edited the comment and made a git PR.
Pushed to 2.1+ Thanks for the patch rabikumar.kc
In the section : http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#hbase.unittests , "Categorizing Tests" -> "Large Tests" needs to be updated to 13 mins. rabikumar.kc please do the needful.
